quran[44]{c,v,t}:
  38,52,and beside them there shall be bashful virgin companions of equal age
  38,53,These are the things which you are being promised on the Day of Reckoning
  38,54,this will be Our provision which will never finish
  38,55,Such will be the reward for the righteous. But for the rebellious there will be an evil resort
  38,56,"hell, that is! In which they will burn - the worst abode"
  38,57,"Such will it be the reward for the wrongdoers. So they will taste scalding water, pus"
  38,58,and other things of the same sort
  38,59,"It will be said to the ringleaders: \"Here are your troops being thrown headlong with you. They are not welcomed here; for they are going to burn in the hellfire"
  38,60,"The followers shall say to their misguided leaders: \"But you! There is no welcome for you either! It was you who have brought us to this end. Such an evil abode"
  38,61,"Then they will pray: \"Our Lord, inflict on those who brought this fate upon us double punishment in the fire"
  38,62,"Then they will say to one another: \"But why do we not see those whom we deemed wicked"
  38,63,and whom we use to ridicule? Or has our eyesight failed to notice them
  38,64,"Surely, this is the very truth: the people in the hellfire will argue just like that"
  38,65,"O Prophet, tell them: \"My mission is only as a Warner; there is no divinity except Allah, the One, the Irresistible"
  38,66,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth and all that lies between them, the Almighty, the Forgiver"
  38,67,"Say: \"This is a supreme message"
  38,68,yet you pay no heed to it
  38,69,"Also say: \"I have no knowledge of that time when the exalted chiefs disputed among themselves"
  38,70,I am informed about all this through a revelation because I am assigned the mission of a plain Warner
  38,71,"Behold when your Lord said to the angels: \"I am about to create a man from clay"
  38,72,"then when I have fashioned him and breathed of My spirit into him, kneel down and prostrate yourselves before him"
  38,73,Accordingly all the angels prostrated themselves
  38,74,except Iblees; he acted arrogantly and became one of the disbelievers
  38,75,"Allah said: \"O Iblees! What prevented you from prostrating yourself to the one whom I have created with My own hands? Are you too arrogant, or do you think that you are one of the exalted ones"
  38,76,"Iblees said: \"I am better than him: You created me from fire and created him from clay"
  38,77,"Allah said: \"Get out of here: for you are accursed"
  38,78,and My curse shall be on you till the Day of Judgment
  38,79,"Iblees said: \"O Lord! Then give me respite till the Day of Resurrection"
  38,80,"Allah said: \"Well, you are given respite"
  38,81,till the Day of Appointed Time
  38,82,"Iblees said: \"I swear by Your Honor, I will mislead them all"
  38,83,except your chosen sincere devotees among them
  38,84,"Allah said: \"Fair enough and now what I am going to say is also fair"
  38,85,that I will fill hell with you and all of those who follow you among them
  38,86,"O Prophet, tell them: \"I do not ask you any recompense for conveying this Message, nor do I pretend to be what I am not"
  38,87,This Qur'an is nothing but a Reminder to all the Worlds
  38,88,"and before long, you will certainly know its truth"
  39,1,"The revelation of this Book (AL-Qur’an) is from Allah, the Almighty, the Wise"
  39,2,"Certainly We have revealed to you the Book with the Truth: therefore worship Allah, offering Him your sincere obedience"
  39,3,"Beware! Sincere true obedience is due to Allah Alone! As for those who take other guardians (worship the saints) besides Him saying: \"We worship them only that they may bring us nearer to Allah.\" Surely Allah will judge between them concerning all that in which they differ. Allah does not guide him who is a liar and a disbeliever"
  39,4,"If Allah had intended to take a son, He could have chosen anyone He pleased out of His creation: Glory be to Him! (He is above such things.) He is Allah, the One, the Irresistible"
  39,5,"He created the heavens and the earth to manifest the Truth. He causes the night to succeed the day and the day to overtake the night. He has subjected the sun and the moon to His law, each one following a course for an appointed term. Is He not the All-Mighty, the All- Forgiving"
  39,6,"He created you all from a single person, then from that person He created his mate. He also created for you eight head of cattle in pairs. He creates you in the wombs of your mothers in stages, one after another, in three layers of darkness. This is Allah, your Lord. To Him belongs the sovereignty. There is no god but Him. How can you then turn away from Him"
  39,7,"If you disbelieve, then you should know that Allah does not need you. He does not like ingratitude from His servants. Therefore, if you are grateful He is pleased with you. On the Day of Judgement, no bearer of burdens will bear the burden of another. Ultimately, all of you have to return to your Lord. Then He will tell you the truth of all that you did in this life. Surely He knows even the secrets of your hearts"